                                         CAPE TOWN - Four South African sailors have been rescued off the coast of Mozambique. The South African Maritime Safety Authority (Samsa) says a yacht sent out a distress signal just before 7am on Friday morning. According to Samsa, the four encountered trouble with their yacht whilst sailing the Indian Ocean. Samsa’s Alma Schutte says: “There were approximately 215km off the coast of Ilha Do Fogo, about 175km directly from shore.”  (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)